The criteria validity of the IES-R for PTSD was examined using ROC analyses (Fig. 1
). The area under the ROC curve was 0.92 (95% confidence interval = 0.88–0.96), which indicated excellent criteria validity for the IES-R in relation to a diagnosis of PTSD. Table 2
shows the criteria validity of the IES-R in terms of sensitivity, specificity, PPV, NPV, and overall misclassification rate (OMR) at various different cutoff points. As the IES-R is treated to be used as a screening tool, which suggests a requirement for greater sensitivity, we suggest that the optimal cutoff point for the IES-R should be 19 of 20, which gives a sensitivity of 85.7%, a specificity of 84.1%, a PPV of 65.2%, a NPV of 94.4%, and an OMR of 15.5%.
